verses.text: After these things Jesus shewed himself again to the disciples at the sea of Tiberias ; and on this wise shewed he \add himself\add*.
There were together Simon Peter , and Thomas called Didymus , and Nathanael of Cana in Galilee , and the \add sons\add* of Zebedee , and two other of his disciples.
Simon Peter saith unto them , I go a fishing. They say unto him , We also go with thee. They went forth , and entered into a ship immediately ; and that night they caught nothing.
But when the morning was now come , Jesus stood on the shore : but the disciples knew not that it was Jesus.
Then Jesus saith unto them , \wj \+w Children|strong="G3813"\+w*, \+w have ye|strong="G2192"\+w* \+w any|strong="G5100"\+w* \+w meat|strong="G4371"\+w*?\wj* They answered him , No.

And he said unto them , \wj \+w Cast|strong="G0906"\+w* \+w the net|strong="G1350"\+w* \+w on|strong="G1519"\+w* \+w the right|strong="G1188"\+w* \+w side|strong="G3313"\+w* \+w of the ship|strong="G4143"\+w*, \+w and|strong="G2532"\+w* \+w ye shall find|strong="G2147"\+w*.\wj* They cast therefore , and now they were not able to draw it for the multitude of fishes.

Therefore that disciple whom Jesus loved saith unto Peter , It is the Lord. Now when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord , he girt \add his\add* fisher’s coat \add unto him\add*, ( for he was naked ,) and did cast himself into the sea.
And the other disciples came in a little ship ; ( for they were not far from land , but as it were two hundred cubits ,) dragging the net with fishes.
As soon then as they were come to land , they saw a fire of coals there , and fish laid thereon , and bread.

Jesus saith unto them , \wj \+w Bring|strong="G5342"\+w* \+w of|strong="G0575"\+w* \+w the fish|strong="G3795"\+w* \+w which|strong="G3739"\+w* \+w ye have|strong="G4084"\+w* \+w now|strong="G3568"\+w* \+w caught|strong="G4084"\+w*.\wj*
Simon Peter went up , and drew the net to land full of great fishes , an hundred and fifty and three : and for all there were so many , yet was not the net broken.
Jesus saith unto them , \wj \+w Come|strong="G1205"\+w* \+add and\+add* \+w dine|strong="G0709"\+w*.\wj* And none of the disciples durst ask him , Who art thou ? knowing that it was the Lord.
Jesus then cometh , and taketh bread , and giveth them , and fish likewise.
This is now the third time that Jesus shewed himself to his disciples , after that he was risen from the dead. \p

¶ So when they had dined , Jesus saith to Simon Peter , \wj \+w Simon|strong="G4613"\+w*, \+add son\+add* \+w of Jonas|strong="G2495"\+w*, \+w lovest thou|strong="G0025"\+w* \+w me|strong="G3165"\+w* \+w more than|strong="G4119"\+w* \+w these|strong="G5130"\+w*?\wj* He saith unto him , Yea , Lord ; thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him , \wj \+w Feed|strong="G4165"\+w* \+w my|strong="G3450"\+w* \+w sheep|strong="G4263"\+w*.\wj*

He saith unto him the third time , \wj \+w Simon|strong="G4613"\+w*, \+add son\+add* \+w of Jonas|strong="G2495"\+w*, \+w lovest thou|strong="G5368"\+w* \+w me|strong="G3165"\+w*?\wj* Peter was grieved because he said unto him the third time , Lovest thou me ? And he said unto him , Lord , thou knowest all things ; thou knowest that I love thee. \wj \+w Verily|strong="G0281"\+w*, \+w verily|strong="G0281"\+w*, \+w I say|strong="G3004"\+w* \+w unto thee|strong="G4671"\+w*, \+w When|strong="G3753"\+w* \+w thou wast|strong="G2258"\+w* \+w young|strong="G3501"\+w*, \+w thou girdedst|strong="G2224"\+w* \+w thyself|strong="G4572"\+w*, \+w and|strong="G2532"\+w* \+w walkedst|strong="G4043"\+w* \+w whither|strong="G3699"\+w* \+w thou wouldest|strong="G2309"\+w*: \+w but|strong="G1161"\+w* \+w when|strong="G3752"\+w* \+w thou shalt be old|strong="G1095"\+w*, \+w thou shalt stretch forth|strong="G1614"\+w* \+w thy|strong="G4675"\+w* \+w hands|strong="G5495"\+w*, \+w and|strong="G2532"\+w* \+w another|strong="G0243"\+w* \+w shall gird|strong="G2224"\+w* \+w thee|strong="G4571"\+w*, \+w and|strong="G2532"\+w* \+w carry|strong="G5342"\+w* \+add thee\+add* \+w whither|strong="G3699"\+w* \+w thou wouldest|strong="G2309"\+w* \+w not|strong="G3756"\+w*.\wj*
This spake he , signifying by what death he should glorify God. And when he had spoken this , he saith unto him , \wj \+w Follow|strong="G0190"\+w* \+w me|strong="G3427"\+w*.\wj*
Then Peter , turning about , seeth the disciple whom Jesus loved following ; which also leaned on his breast at supper , and said , Lord , which is he that betrayeth thee ?
Peter seeing him saith to Jesus , Lord , and what \add shall\add* this man \add do\add*?

Jesus saith unto him , \wj \+w If|strong="G1437"\+w* \+w I will that|strong="G2309"\+w* \+w he|strong="G0846"\+w* \+w tarry|strong="G3306"\+w* \+w till|strong="G2193"\+w* \+w I come|strong="G2064"\+w*, \+w what|strong="G5101"\+w* \+add is that\+add* \+w to|strong="G4314"\+w* \+w thee|strong="G4571"\+w*? \+w follow|strong="G0190"\+w* \+w thou|strong="G4771"\+w* \+w me|strong="G3427"\+w*.\wj*

Then went this saying abroad among the brethren , that that disciple should not die : yet Jesus said not unto him , He shall not die ; but , If I will that he tarry till I come , what \add is that\add* to thee ?
This is the disciple which testifieth of these things , and wrote these things : and we know that his testimony is true.
And there are also many other things which Jesus did , the which , if they should be written every one , I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that should be written. Amen.
